China Development Bank  Corp., the
state-owned policy lender, said its outstanding foreign currency
loans reached $150 billion at the end of March.  Asset quality continues to be good, the bank said in a
notice on its website. China Development Bank had $141.3 billion
of outstanding foreign currency loans at the end of last year,
rising from $64.5 billion in 2008.  Total outstanding loans at the bank reached 4.7 trillion
yuan at the end of the first quarter, it said, with a non-
performing loan ratio of 0.58 percent.  -- Henry Sanderson . Editors:  To contact the reporter on this story:
